ation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Heng</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">Y</span></span>, Schuffler MD, Haggitt RC, Rohrmann CA. Pneumatosis intestinalis: a review. <em>Am J Gastroenterol</em>1995; 90: 1747–1758.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/7572888/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Am+J+Gastroenterol&amp;publication_year=1995&amp;pages=1747&amp;pmid=7572888">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">12.</div><div id="R12" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Jamart</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">J</span></span>. Pneumatosis cystoides intestinalis: a statistical study of 919 cases. <em>Acta Hepatogastroenterol (Stuttg)</em>1979; 26: 419–422.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/525221/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Acta+Hepatogastroenterol+%28Stuttg%29&amp;publication_year=1979&amp;pages=419&amp;pmid=525221">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">13.</div><div id="R13" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-firstauthor"><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-snm">Pickhardt</span><span class="named-content" data-type="arthw-fnm">PJ</span></span>, Kim DH, Taylor AJ. Asymptomatic pneumatosis at CT colonography: a self-limited incidental imaging finding distinct from perforation. Presented 